The Keiser Report  No. 239
= Max Keiser and Stacy Herbert =
Saturday, 21 January 2012


[sebaygo1]


This time Max and Stacy discuss captains of the financial industry abandoning ship while tripping into TARP. In the second half of the show, Max talks to former oil market regulator, Chris Cook, about the imminent collapse of the oil market and about the role of Goldman Sachs, BP and passive investors in driving the price of oil.
